The paper deals with the problem of selecting a representative subset of a dataset based on rankings, which is a common task in data exploration. This problem is related to several subfields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC). However, given that the paper proposes a geometric interpretation of items and utilizes combinatorial geometry notions for developing approximation algorithms, it is most likely to belong to the cs.DS sub-category.
